# CR-01: SQL injection in __sv_compute_create_from_yaml is eliminated by
# replacing `Connection::Query("SELECT content FROM read_text('<path>')")`
# with a direct DuckDB `FileSystem::OpenFile` call (D-01). The
# `enable_external_access` setting is honoured by LocalFileSystem natively,
# so the new path stays gated on the same setting as the old one (D-02/D-03).
#
# Future assertions (Plan 07 populates):
#   B1: `SET enable_external_access = false;` followed by
#       `CREATE SEMANTIC VIEW v FROM YAML FILE '/tmp/x.yaml'` MUST raise a
#       `statement error` block whose tail contains a substring confirming
#       the access gate (likely "external access is disabled" or similar
#       DuckDB-native wording from the FileSystem layer).
#   B2: With `enable_external_access = true` (the default) and a valid
#       on-disk YAML file, the same statement MUST succeed — confirms the
#       FileSystem-direct read path is functional, not just permissive of
#       the gate.

require semantic_views

statement ok
LOAD semantic_views;

# Stub no-op so the runner does not error on an empty file.
statement ok
SELECT 1;

